# Git commit identity

When creating git commits in this repository (or RXDK-Libs / RXDK-Tools submodules):

- **Never** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or any Cursor/agent co-author trailer.
- **Never** set author/committer to Cursor, Cursor Agent, or `cursoragent@cursor.com`.
- Use the user's normal git identity only (`EqUiNoX` / their configured `user.name` and `user.email`).
- Commit messages should contain only the human-written summary and body — no agent attribution lines.

If a commit command would append a co-author trailer, remove it before running `git commit`.

The repo `.githooks/prepare-commit-msg` strips Cursor co-author lines if the IDE injects them; `.githooks/commit-msg` rejects any that remain. Run `.\scripts\setup-git-hooks.ps1` once to enable hooks.
